HEADWORD: Interpone
<hw>In`ter*pone"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>interponere</ets>; <ets>inter</ets> between + <ets>ponere</ets> to
place. See <er>Position</er>.]</ety> <def>To interpose; to insert or
place between.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark> <rj><au>Cudworth.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

